&gt; Hi Jeff,
&gt; for the past few months I&#39;ve been catching up on the NN topic.  I found a
&gt; great book by Hagan, Demuth and Beale, &quot;Neural Network Design&quot;.  They go
&gt; through explanation of different networks and math treatment.  I found it very
&gt; easy to read (enjoyable at times) and math is very straight forward.  They
&gt; make use of Matlab&#39;s NN toolbox and provide number of examples (which I found
&gt; useless at best).  From what I&#39;ve read this book is considered a good intro
&gt; into the field of NN.
&gt; You can find goodbook reviews and suggestions at ai-depot.com  ai depot also
&gt; has some code in c++ that you can toy around with.  If you want free books
&gt; consider genalgo.com
&gt; http://www.genalgo.com/NEURAL_NETWORK/BOOKS/REINFORCEMENT_LEARNING/the-book.ht
&gt; ml
&gt; this is a link to a book on reinforcement learning.  Work you way backwards
&gt; and you&#39;ll find some more interesting books.  Also, consider using a library
&gt; in your school.  You can always have them purchase the books :)
&gt; 
&gt; Aleks
